{title: Faded Coat Of Blue}
{artist: The Waller Brothers}
{composer: Written by J.H. McNaughton}

[C]My brave man sleeps in his [F]faded coat of blue
In a [C]lonely grave unknown lies a [G7]heart that beat so true
He [C]sat faint and hungry [F]among the Spanish braves
And they [C]laid him sad and lonely with[G7]in a nameless [C]grave
No more the bugle calls the weary [F]one
[G7]Rest noble spirit in a grave unknown
For we'll [C]find you and know you [F]among the good and true
Where a [C]robe of white is given for a [G7]faded coat of [C]blue
He cried give me water and [F]just a little crumb
And my [C]mother she would bless you through [G7]all the years to come
And [C]tell my sweet sister so [F]gentle good and true
That I'll [C]meet her up in heaven in my [G7]faded coat of [C]blue
repeat #2
He said my dear comrade you [F]cannot bear me home
But [C]you'll mark my name for mother she'll [G7]find me and she'll come
I [C]fear she'll not know me [F]among the good and true
When I [C]meet her up in heaven in my [G7]faded coat of [C]blue
repeat #2 x2